title: Georgia Firm Recalls More Ready-To-Eat Products for Possible Listeria Contamination
summary: Editor's Note: This recall release is being reissued to expand the July 19, 2011 recall to include additional products. WASHINGTON, July 26, 2011- Flying Food Group, LLC, a Lawrenceville, Ga., establishment, is expanding its recall of ready-to-eat chicken, turkey, beef and pork products by an...
impacted_products: 8.4-ounce packages of "STARBUCKS CHIPOTLE CHICKEN WRAPS Bistro Box" that have an "Enjoy by" dates of 7/16-7/26 stamped on the package.
